thread.title: Industria full-year profit falls 26pc though leasing pipeline remains strong
thread.title_full: Industria full-year profit falls 26pc though leasing pipeline remains strong | afr.com

author: Su-Lin Tan
title: Industria full-year profit falls 26pc though leasing pipeline remains strong
text:
Industria REIT said its gross revenue in the year ended June 30 rose 17.4 per cent to $39 million in from $33 million a year ago. Glenn Hunt Share on twitter Share on Google Plus by Su-Lin Tan Industria REIT's full-year profit has tumbled 26 per cent to $23 million from $31 million last year because of lower-than-expected rental income, the sale of assets and a fall in fair value adjustments on investment properties compared with a year ago.
While profit was down, the REIT's gross revenue rose 17.4 per cent to $39 million in the year ended June 30 from $33 million a year ago.
The REIT sold 53 Brandl Street and 21 Brandl Street in Brisbane Technology Park at a premium to their combined carrying value of $10.2 million.
At the November annual general meeting, the REIT announced a deterioration the Brisbane rental market with higher-than-forecast vacancy periods and lower than forecast rental income at the Brisbane Technology Park and at Rhodes Building C, NSW.
In fiscal 2015, the fund renewed or leased more than 18,800 square metres in leasing space. After transactions such as the 10,647-sq m lease at 32 Garden Street, Kilsyth and the 2859-sq m lease to Toyota Australia at Unit F, 5 Butler Boulevard, Adelaide Airport, the REIT's portfolio WALE is 5.3 years and occupancy rate is 94.4 per cent.
Other new leases include the 416-sq m office tenancy to Interactive at 7 Clunies Ross Court, Brisbane Technology Park, 420-sq m office tenancy to ABC Consulting at Rhodes Building C, 401-sq m office tenancy to Nexon at 6 Electronics Street, Brisbane Technology Park and the 350-sq m office tenancy to Wiley & Co. at Rhodes Building C.
Industria's gearing is 33.4 per cent, within the target range of 30 per cent to 40 per cent.
The REIT has projected it will make a distribution of between 15¢ to 15.8¢ a security.
